# "On this page" purpose box

Every AJO user-guide page must open with a shaded "On this page" box: a one-sentence
statement of the page's purpose, placed immediately after the H1. It helps human readers
and AI tools understand the page before reading. Tracked under epic DOCAC-14936.

## Exact format

```text
# Page Title {#anchor}

>[!BEGINSHADEBOX]

**On this page:** <one clear sentence describing the page's purpose>

>[!ENDSHADEBOX]

...original content...
```

## Rules

- Place it directly after the **first H1**, and **before** any existing `>[!CONTEXTUALHELP]` block.
- Exactly **one blank line** between the H1 and `>[!BEGINSHADEBOX]`, and after `>[!ENDSHADEBOX]`.
- The sentence: **exactly one sentence**, plain text, American English. No links, `[!UICONTROL]`, or bold other than the `**On this page:**` label.
- Make it accurate to the actual page; reuse/adapt the frontmatter `description` as the seed.
- **Idempotent**: never add a second box if one already follows the H1.
- Never modify frontmatter or other content.

## Scope

In scope: all pages under `help/`. **Exclude** reference/syntax pages: any `*/api-reference/*`,
`building-journeys/expression/`, `building-journeys/functions/`, `personalization/functions/`.

## Tooling

- Insert: `python scripts/on-this-page/add_on_this_page.py <path> --seed-from-description`
- Validate: `python scripts/on-this-page/validate_on_this_page.py <path> --require`
